7 on our list: Duke football defeats the Hurricanes in Miami for the first time since 1976, clinching its sixth bowl appearance in seven years.
Duke football truly had no reason to be confident heading into Hard Rock Stadium for its meeting with the Hurricanes.
But soon, the rain began pouring down, turning the surface into a more of a slip ‘n slide than football field.
But All-American linebacker Joe Giles-Harris—who recorded a game-high 12 tackles in the contest—blocked the kick, keeping the Blue Devils’ deficit at two.
But the Miami win represents a bright spot, the Blue Devils’ first victory overall against the Hurricanes since 2013.